laboratory_examinations.findings: Increased liver echogenicity likely from fatty deposition; 8mm echogenicity in liver consistent with hemangioma. No CBD dilatation or evidence of cholecystitis.

laboratory_examinations.procedure_name: CT Abdomen and Pelvis with Contrast
laboratory_examinations.findings: Peripancreatic inflammation involving the head and body with heterogeneous enhancement; small-to-moderate peripancreatic fluid; 8mm hypodense lesion in left interpolar kidney likely representing a simple cyst.
